folder: 69th Street (East) & Marie Curie Avenue, Manhattan, NY
text:
537 East 69th Street, north side, adjoining and west of the N.W. corner of Marie Curie Avenue. This building will soon be demolished to make way for the Cornell University -- New York Hospital buildings.

February 13, 1928.

P. L. Sperr.

folder: 69th Street (East) & Marie Curie Avenue, Manhattan, NY
text:
537 East 69th Street, north side, adjoining and west of the N.W. corner of Marie Curie Avenue. This building, the former Hammond Typewriter building, will soon be demolished to make way for the Cornell-University -- New York Hospital buildings.

February 13, 1928.

P. L. Sperr.
